<heading id="BF3A81D3FFF7F970B1E72CDD518EFA40" bold="true" box="[151,740,1410,1437]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" reason="1">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B1E72CDD518EFA40" bold="true" box="[151,740,1410,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF7F970B03A2CDC518EFA40" authority="Moure, 1945" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1945" box="[330,740,1410,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Hemisiella">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B03A2CDC52C8FA41" bold="true" box="[330,418,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0C32CDC515FFA41" bold="true" box="[435,565,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B3362CDD518EFA40" author="Moure" box="[582,740,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S. (1945) Apoidea da colecao do Conde Amadeu A. Barbiellini. II. (Hym. Apoidea). Revista de Entomologia, 16, 394 - 414." type="journal article" year="1945">Moure, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACD76534FFF7F970B1E72C9756F6F804" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" type="description">
<paragraph id="E47236BFFFF7F970B1E72C975260F9AF" blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF7F970B04D2C9451ABFA3F" authority="Moure, 1945" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1945" box="[317,705,1481,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Hemisiella">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B04D2C9452FAFA3C" box="[317,400,1482,1505]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0D22C975171FA3F" box="[418,539,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B35E2C9451ABFA3F" author="Moure" box="[558,705,1481,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S. (1945) Apoidea da colecao do Conde Amadeu A. Barbiellini. II. (Hym. Apoidea). Revista de Entomologia, 16, 394 - 414." type="journal article" year="1945">Moure, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a lineage that comprises 18 species widely distributed in the New World, ranging from southern 
<collectingCountry id="9CDA762FFFF7F970B33E2CB35186F9DB" box="[590,748,1517,1542]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B2722CB35742F9DB" author="Pemberton" box="[770,1064,1517,1542]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Pemberton, R. W. &amp; Liu, H. (2008) Naturalization of the oil collecting bee Centris nitida (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Centridini), a potential pollinator of selected native, ornamental, and invasive plants in Florida. Florida Entomologist, 91, 101 - 109. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1653 / 0015 - 4040 (2008) 091 [0101: NOTOCB] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2008">Pemberton &amp; Liu, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry id="9CDA762FFFF7F970B5132CB357BFF9DB" box="[1123,1237,1517,1542]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, including some Caribbean islands (
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B01E2F4C512FF9F7" author="Moure" box="[366,581,1553,1578]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0B12F4C5298F9F7" box="[449,498,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). As it occurs with other lineages of 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF7F970B2912F4C575EF9F4" box="[993,1076,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B2912F4C575EF9F4" box="[993,1076,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the highest species diversity of this subgenus is in tropical areas of South America, where up to 13 of the known species can be found (
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B4432F685395F9AF" author="Moure" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B4F82F6853C7F9AF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E47236BFFFF7F970B1B72F2350DBF897" blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The species of 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0062F2052E3F948" box="[374,393,1662,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0D32F235176F94B" box="[419,540,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) are morphologically homogeneous and can be recognized by their pattern of facial coloration in both sexes. Although some authors have considered 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B2B32FFC50BCF964" box="[963,982,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B29D2FFF570CF967" box="[1005,1126,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) as a junior synonym of 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B4F22FFC56FFF964" box="[1410,1429,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B1D02F985253F900" box="[160,313,1734,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B03A2F9B5297F903" author="Cockerell" box="[330,509,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1899) Notes on the nomenclature of some Hymenoptera. The Entomologist, 32, 14." type="journal article" year="1899">Cockerell, 1899</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B37C2F9B5195F903" author="Griswold" box="[524,767,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Griswold, T., Hanson, P. E. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos, I. (2006) Las abejas. In: Hanson, P. E. &amp; Gauld, I. D. (Eds.), Hymenoptera de la Region Neotropical. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 77, pp. 734 - 785." type="journal article" year="2006">
Griswold 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B30D2F9851C5F903" box="[637,687,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B27C2F9B50AAF903" author="Michener" box="[780,960,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Michener, C. D. (2007) The Bees of the World. 2 nd Edition. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, 992 pp." type="book" year="2007">Michener, 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B2BB2F9B57D5F903" author="Gonzalez" box="[971,1215,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Gonzalez, V. H., Ascher, J. S. &amp; Engel, M. S. (2012) A new Stelis (Dolichostelis) from northern Colombia (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae): first records for South America and a synopsis of the bee fauna from the Caribbean region of Colombia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 2919 - 2934. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2012.738835" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gonzalez 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B54C2F985707F903" box="[1084,1133,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2012
</bibRefCitation>
), the species of this subgenus form a distinct monophyletic group which is closely related to the subgenera 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B50B2FB457E4F8DC" box="[1147,1166,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B5D62FB45655F8DC" box="[1190,1343,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) and 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B4F22FB456FFF8DC" box="[1410,1429,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B1D02E53526FF8FB" box="[160,261,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Trachina</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B0652E5352FCF8FB" author="Klug" box="[277,406,1805,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1807) Kritische Revision der Bienengattungen in Fabricius neuem Piezatensysteme mit Berucksichtigung der Kirbyschen Bienefamilien und Illiger's Bemerkunde zu Kirbys Monographie. Magazin fur Insektenkunde, 6, 200 - 228." type="journal article" year="1807">Klug, 1807</bibRefCitation>
, with which it shares several morphological synapomorphies in the male (Vivallo &amp; Melo in preparation). Thus, we recognized C. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B3372E6F51AAF897" box="[583,704,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) as a valid subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E47236BFFFF7F970B1B72E0B56F6F804" blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The males of 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B02E2E08521BF8B0" box="[350,369,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B0F72E0B516AF8B3" box="[391,512,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) are characterized by a spine-shaped projection on the hind trochanter, and a broad yellow transverse spot on the clypeus (covering the clypeus entirely in 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF7F970B2C92E245641F84F" authority="Burmeister, 1876" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1876" box="[953,1323,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B2C92E2450A6F84C" box="[953,972,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B2AA2E245736F84C" box="[986,1116,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">nigriventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF7F970B5152E275641F84F" author="Burmeister" box="[1125,1323,1913,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Burmeister, H. (1876) Hymenopterologische Mittheilungen. Stettinger Entomologische Zeitung, 37, 151 - 183." type="journal article" year="1876">Burmeister, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Females have an elliptical primary basitibial plate with the secondary plate covered with dense, short pubescence, and a dark brown to black clypeus with two very large, oblique yellow patches (which may be joined medially in 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF7F970B4F22E9C56FFF804" box="[1410,1429,1986,2009]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACD76534FFF4F973B1E729C75150FE29" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="E47236BFFFF4F973B1E729C750A3FEC0" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF4F973B1E729C752F0FF6D" authority="Perez, 1905" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,410,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B1E729C75267FF6D" box="[151,269,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">transversa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF4F973B06329C652F0FF6D" author="Perez" box="[275,410,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Perez, J. (1905) Hymenopteres nouveaux du Mexique. Bulletin, Museum d'Historie Naturalle, 11, 39 - 41." type="journal article" year="1905">Pérez, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF4F973B27F29C650FDFF6D" box="[783,919,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merrillae">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B27F29C65048FF72" box="[783,802,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B25F29C950FDFF6D" box="[815,919,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">merrillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="23CD4D3CFFF4F973B2BD29C6579FFF6D" authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[973,1269,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B2BD29C6508AFF72" box="[973,992,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B29D29C7575FFF6D" box="[1005,1077,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">vittata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="805C4B4EFFF4F973B54B29C9579FFF6D" author="Lepeletier" box="[1083,1269,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Species of 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B4F229C656F6FF72" box="[1410,1436,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B1D029E25273FF08" box="[160,281,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) nest in pre-existing cavities in wood as in the subgenera 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B2BB29E350B4FF09" box="[971,990,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B28929E357F8FF09" box="[1017,1170,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) and 
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B5A929E35786FF09" box="[1241,1260,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="D6B9EAADFFF4F973B47629E256F8FF08" box="[1286,1426,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Xanthemisia</emphasis>
) 
